rComments: Do your practice tests, he uses some of the same multiple choices from the previous years. Read your textbook, classes are boring, but it's easy to have a good grade.

Super boring lectures, basically copy pasted out of the textbook. If you read it and understand it, it's definitely not worth it to go to class.  He gave "practice" exams on Blackboard before both midterms, and they were 90% identical.  Really easy to get 100% on the midterms if you do those, he'll correct them for you by email.
